 Goliath Film and Media Holdings Announces Acquisition of Distribution Rights to Educational Film 
         










    










 






 











 









Goliath Film and Media Holdings Announces Acquisition of Distribution Rights to Educational Film Library

Apr 11, 2012, 09:00 ET
		  		  						
						 from   Goliath Film and Media Holdings 











 
















































 

 




















 


LOS ANGELES, April 11, 2012 /PRNewswire/ -- Goliath Film and Media Holdings  (OTC Bulletin Board:   GFMH) announces that it has acquired the worldwide, five year distribution rights to approximately 1500 educational films. These include English as a Second Language and mathematics instructional materials, among others. The films can be used on a stand-alone basis as an online instructional course, or as an adjunct to traditional instructional classes. 
According to the US Department of Education, there are 5.4 million limited English proficient (LEP) students in the US, with one in four students expected to be LEP students by 2025. The No Child Left Behind Act, Title III, provides for supplemental Federal funding of LEP programs for local school districts. Federal funding of English learner programs in the 2011 Federal budget was over $700 million. School districts are also faced with shrinking financial resources to duplicate Goliath's unique instructional library; Goliath believes that its educational library, which has already met LAUSD standards, will be very attractive with school districts seeking to improve their LEP curriculum on a cost effective basis.    
Goliath intends to distribute these films as well to the huge English as a Second Language educational industry abroad, and also to offer them on a streaming basis under subscription in selected markets. Estimates of the number of persons worldwide learning English range from 300 million on up, with English ability becoming an employment prerequisite throughout Asia. Goliath will be actively marketing these films throughout the world in 2012. 
This acquisition is the first step in Goliath's building its film and media library. Over the next 90 days, Goliath intends to acquire additional educational films and to add hundreds of titles to its film libraries in the niche markets of faith-based, responsible minority content, and horror, for worldwide distribution. 
Also, on April 10, 2012, the Chief Executive Officer of Goliath, Lamont Roberts, was interviewed by Stock Traders Talk Radio. The audio transcript of the interview can be found at http://stocktraderstalk.com/stt-radio-gfmh-ceo-interview-04102012-0.   
About Goliath Film and Media
Goliath Film and Media Holdings ("Goliath"), through its wholly-owned subsidiary Goliath Film and Media International, intends to develop and distribute film content with an emphasis on "niche" markets of the entertainment industry, such as, without limitation, education, horror, faith-based, and socially responsible minority content.  Goliath will specialize in licensing quality films. Goliath also intends to develop screenplays with the intent of outsourcing the production, and locking in the distribution rights to the films produced through the Company's development efforts. Goliath plans to license films domestically and internationally, through a wide distribution network to include major exhibitors, distributors and television networks. Our website is www.goliathfilmandmediainternational.com.
Safe Harbor                           
This News Release may contain "forward-looking statements" within the meaning of Section 27A of the Securities Act of 1933, and Section 21E of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934. Although the Company believes that the expectations reflected in such forward-looking statements are reasonable, it can give no assurance that such expectations will prove correct. 
 SOURCE  Goliath Film and Media Holdings  

RELATED LINKS
http://www.goliathfilmandmediainternational.com



  

